qas.question: On what continent did the Ottoman Navy contribute most?

context: The Ottoman Navy vastly contributed to the expansion of the Empire's territories on the <a0_0>European continent<a0_0/>. It initiated the conquest of <a1_0>North Africa<a1_0/>, with the addition of Algeria and Egypt to the Ottoman Empire in <a2_0>1517<a2_0/>. Starting with the loss of Greece in <a3_0>1821<a3_0/> and <a4_0>Algeria<a4_0/> in 1830, Ottoman naval power and control over the Empire's distant overseas territories began to decline. Sultan Abdülaziz (reigned 1861–1876) attempted to reestablish a strong Ottoman navy, building the largest fleet after those of Britain and France. The shipyard at Barrow, England, built its first submarine in 1886 for the Ottoman Empire.
